Response: We thank the reviewer for this concern. We report statistical evidence below, followed by revised experimental results.
On S3DIS Area 5, PointSS achieves 73.8% ±0.37% over 8 independent runs (73.2, 73.4, 73.6, 73.8, 73.8, 74.0, 74.1, 74.3). 6 out of 8 runs exceed PTv3's reported result (73.4%). We further reproduced PTv3 three times under identical settings; all three runs yielded results below 73.4%, suggesting the reported PTv3 figure may represent the upper bound of its variance. One-sample t-tests confirm statistical significance: t(7)=2.90, p=0.011 vs. PTv3 (73.4%); t(7)=2.14, p=0.035 vs. Pamba (73.5%).
